<p>When I am coding in c++, I want vim to expand <code>(</code> into <code>()&lt;++&gt;</code> and place the cursor in the parenthesis. I do this by putting the following line in one of the files loaded at startup:</p>  <pre><code>inoremap (      ()&lt;++&gt;&lt;Left&gt;&lt;Left&gt;&lt;Left&gt;&lt;Left&gt;&lt;Left&gt; </code></pre>  <p>However, I would like this binding to be disabled in comments, like</p>  <pre><code>// Inline comment where ( shouldn't become ()&lt;++&gt; </code></pre>  <p>or </p>  <pre><code>/* Comment block where ( shouldn't become ()&lt;++&gt; */ </code></pre>  <p>How can I do it?</p>